      "targetText": "Copiază rezultatele!"
    }
  ],
  "learningTips": [
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The English word “copy” sounds like the Romanian “a copia,” both meaning to reproduce or duplicate something."
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Remember the phrase “copy and paste” from computers to link the English verb “copy” with the Romanian “a copia.”"
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Think of the English word “copycat” to recall the meaning of “a copia” as imitating or duplicating."
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Practice conjugating “a copia” with simple sentences like “Eu copiez” (I copy), “Am copiat” (I copied), and “Voi copia” (I will copy)."
    }
  ],
